programme.desc: A businessman's wife tries to kill him, having her lover throw him over a cliff, but the lover instead is killed in a fiery car accident. The businessman, assumed dead, lays low in a town waiting for his conniving wife to be sentenced to death for his murder. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Lady From Shanghai
programme.desc: An Irish seaman who hires on to a yacht sailing from New York to San Francisco with a beautiful seductress finds himself in the middle of a murder plot against her husband. The film-noir thriller is famous for its climactic scene in a hall of mirrors. Orson Welles stars, directed and wrote the screenplay. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Breaking Point
programme.desc: A financially strapped charter-boat skipper becomes involved with smugglers in and effort to keep up payments on his vessel and soon finds himself in over his head. An adaptation of Ernest Hemingway's "To Have and Have Not." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Crossfire
programme.desc: One of the first major-studio efforts to confront anti-Semitism, this Best Picture nominee is a film-noir account of a quartet of GIs who get involved in the murder of a Jewish Army veteran. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: I Wake Up Screaming
programme.desc: A homicide victim's sister and a well-known New York promoter are the prime suspects in the murder of an aspiring model and would-be actress that he had groomed for stardom. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Vicki
programme.desc: A supermodel gets murdered. While investigating the case the story of a waitress turned glamor girl is revealed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Affair in Trinidad
programme.desc: When her husband is murdered, nightclub dancer Chris meets and gets involved with her late husband's friend Max. Her brother-in-law Steve starts his own investigation and believes Max is the killer. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Niagara
programme.desc: An adulterous wife purposely flaunts her sexuality to drive her jealous husband into a rage so that her lover will kill him. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Las Vegas Story
programme.desc: A robbery scheme set to take place in Las Vegas results in murder, and a woman and her new husband encounter her ex, a policeman trying to crack the case. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Deadline at Dawn
programme.desc: A sailor on leave is mistakenly charged with murder and has until dawn to prove that he didn't do it. He receives unexpected help from a world-weary dance-hall girl. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Enemy Below
programme.desc: A World War II battle of wits between an American destroyer captain and a German U-Boat commander in the North Atlantic. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Yearling
programme.desc: Coming-of-age Best Picture nominee is based on Marjorie Kinnan Rawlings' Pulitzer Prize-winning novel about impoverished backwoods farmers in 1878 Florida, where the young son takes it upon himself to care for an orphaned fawn, but the animal's wild nature forces the boy to make a most difficult decision. As the lad's parents, Gregory Peck and Jane Wyman were nominated for Best Actor and Actress. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Chisum
programme.desc: A New Mexico cattle baron and a ranch foreman battle over land with a greedy rival during the Lincoln County War in the 1870s. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Stone Killer
programme.desc: A detective uncovers an aging Sicilian Mafioso's revenge plot to employ Vietnam vets as assassins. Based on the novel "A Complete State of Death" by John Gardner. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Assault on Precinct 13
programme.desc: Cops, secretaries and prisoners are trapped in a soon-to-be-shuttered Los Angeles police station and forced to fight off a horde of murderous gang members who are heavily armed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Hard Time
programme.desc: A world-weary cop battles to clear his name after being framed for murder. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Valachi Papers
programme.desc: A violent look at organized crime in America, from 1929 to the 1960s, through the eyes of mobster Jon Valachi. After a near-successful attempt on his life in prison, Valachi is convinced by a federal agent to become a mob informant. Based on the novel by Peter Maas.(n)
